$ cquad4_free_thermal.bdf
$ Single CQUAD4 — free thermal expansion with zero stress
$
$ Geometry: 1 m × 1 m square plate, t = 0.1 m
$ Material: E = 1e6 Pa, nu = 0.3, alpha = 1e-5 /°C
$ Load:     uniform temperature T = 100 °C (T_ref = 0 → ΔT = 100 °C)
$ BCs:      minimal rigid-body suppression only:
$             fix T1+T2 of node 1 (origin)
$             fix T2 of node 2 (on x-axis, prevents rotation about z)
$             fix T1 of node 4 (on y-axis, consistent with free expansion)
$
$ All BCs are compatible with the free-expansion field
$   u = alpha*ΔT*x,  v = alpha*ΔT*y
$ so stresses must be zero.
$
$ Expected displacements (alpha*ΔT = 1e-5 * 100 = 1e-3):
$   node 2 at (1,0): u = 1e-3 m
$   node 3 at (1,1): u = 1e-3 m, v = 1e-3 m
$   node 4 at (0,1): v = 1e-3 m
$
SOL 101
CEND
SUBCASE 1
  LABEL = FREE THERMAL EXPANSION
  LOAD = 1
  SPC = 1
  DISPLACEMENT = ALL
  STRESS = ALL
BEGIN BULK
PARAM,CSVOUT,YES
$ Nodes
GRID,1,,0.0,0.0,0.0
GRID,2,,1.0,0.0,0.0
GRID,3,,1.0,1.0,0.0
GRID,4,,0.0,1.0,0.0
$ Material: alpha = 1e-5 /°C, ref_temp = 0
MAT1,1,1.0E6,,0.3,0.0,1.0E-5,0.0
$ Shell property
PSHELL,1,1,0.1
$ Element
CQUAD4,1,1,1,2,3,4
$ Minimal BCs (all compatible with free thermal field u=alpha*dT*x, v=alpha*dT*y)
SPC1,1,12,1
SPC1,1,2,2
SPC1,1,1,4
$ Uniform temperature T = 100 °C on all nodes
TEMP,1,1,100.0
TEMP,1,2,100.0
TEMP,1,3,100.0
TEMP,1,4,100.0
ENDDATA
